      "id": "akala",
      "front": "eat (he eats)",
      "back": "يأكل",
      "romanized": "ya'kul",
      "grammarNote": "يـ prefix marks masculine singular present. أكَلَ (akala) is the root (he ate). Present tense: يأكل (he eats), تأكل (she eats / you eat), أكل (I eat)."
    },
    {
